#. <section class="sutta" id="sn8.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn8.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Vaṅgīsavagga"
msgstr "1. With Vaṅgīsa"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 3. Pesalasutta → pesalāatimaññanāsuttaṃ (bj) | pesalātimaññanāsuttaṃ (s1-3) | pesalāatimaññanā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn8.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Pesalasutta"
msgstr "3. Good-Hearted"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.403"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.3:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā vaṅgīso āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye āyasmatā "
"nigrodhakappena upajjhāyena saddhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Vaṅgīsa was staying near Āḷavī, at the Aggāḷava Tree-"
"shrine, together with his mentor, Venerable Nigrodhakappa."

# I think BB’s “well-behaved” for pesala leans too heavily on the comm’s punning “piya-sila”, and sounds a bit patronizing. I think it’s more of an emotional quality.
msgctxt "sn8.3:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā vaṅgīso attano paṭibhānena aññe pesale bhikkhū "
"atimaññati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Vaṅgīsa looked down on other good-hearted "
"mendicants because of his own poetic virtuosity."

msgctxt "sn8.3:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato vaṅgīsassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

msgctxt "sn8.3:1.4"
msgid ""
"“alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ; "
msgstr "“It’s my loss, my misfortune, "

msgctxt "sn8.3:1.5"
msgid "yvāhaṃ attano paṭibhānena aññe pesale bhikkhū atimaññāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"that I look down on other good-hearted mendicants because of my own poetic "
"virtuosity.”"

msgctxt "sn8.3:1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā vaṅgīso attanāva attano vippaṭisāraṃ uppādetvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ "
"imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, on the occasion of arousing remorse in himself, he recited these "
"verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.3:2.1"
msgid "“Mānaṃ pajahassu gotama,"
msgstr "“Give up conceit, Gotama!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:2.2"
msgid "Mānapathañca pajahassu;"
msgstr "Completely abandon the different kinds of conceit!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:2.3"
msgid "Asesaṃ mānapathasmiṃ,"
msgstr "Besotted with the different kinds of conceit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:2.4"
msgid "Samucchito vippaṭisārīhuvā cirarattaṃ."
msgstr "you’ve had regrets for a long time."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.3:3.1"
msgid "Makkhena makkhitā pajā,"
msgstr "Smeared by smears and slain by conceit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:3.2"
msgid "Mānahatā nirayaṃ papatanti;"
msgstr "people fall into hell."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:3.3"
msgid "Socanti janā cirarattaṃ,"
msgstr "When people slain by conceit are reborn in hell,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:3.4"
msgid "Mānahatā nirayaṃ upapannā."
msgstr "they grieve for a long time."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.3:4.1"
msgid "Na hi socati bhikkhu kadāci,"
msgstr "But a mendicant who practices rightly,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:4.2"
msgid "Maggajino sammāpaṭipanno;"
msgstr "owning the path, never grieves."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:4.3"
msgid "Kittiñca sukhañca anubhoti,"
msgstr "They enjoy happiness and a good reputation,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:4.4"
msgid "Dhammadasoti tamāhu pahitattaṃ."
msgstr "and they rightly call him a ‘Seer of Truth’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.188"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.3:5.1"
msgid "Tasmā akhilodha padhānavā,"
msgstr "So don’t be hard-hearted, be energetic,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:5.2"
msgid "Nīvaraṇāni pahāya visuddho;"
msgstr "with hindrances given up, be pure."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:5.3"
msgid "Mānañca pahāya asesaṃ,"
msgstr "Then with conceit given up completely,"

# As per BB’s note, I see this verse as expressing a gradual sequence, and have made this more explicit in translation.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.3:5.4"
msgid "Vijjāyantakaro samitāvī”ti."
msgstr "use knowledge to make an end, and be at peace.”"
